neighborhood_overview:
English:
The colony is divided in two: Escandón I and Escandón II, due to its great extension. The first section is located from Avenida Patriotismo and adjoins the colony Tacubaya; While Section II extends from the Pte. Miguel Alemán Viaduct and adjoins the Colonia Condesa.

The colony still conserves great part of the constructions that correspond to the first half of century XX, emphasizing styles like: Californian colonial, and neocolonial. To the north, given the proximity to the town of Tacubaya, are located some examples of constructions that correspond to the eclectic architecture. Most of the buildings built in the middle of the 20th century correspond to apartment buildings.

The property is around 1.9 km from National Museum of Anthropology, 2.3 km from The Angel of Independence and 3.4 km from United States Embassy. The guest house has family rooms.

Chapultepec Forest is 4.2 km from Casa Melgar, while Museo de Memoria y Tolerancia is 5 km from the property. The nearest airport is Benito Juarez International Airport, 10 km from the accommodation.

Condesa is one of Mexico City’s most attractive locales. It’s packed with nice restaurants and boutiques and a vibrant nightlife. The house itself is set on a quiet street providing a peaceful respite. Many museums, galleries and shops are nearby too.

neighborhood_overview:
San Pedro de los Pinos is an emblematic neighborhood located in the heart of vibrant Mexico City. With a perfect blend of tradition and modernity, this neighborhood captivates visitors with its historical charm and contemporary amenities.

The neighborhood boasts a privileged location, making it an ideal destination for those who want to explore the best of the city. Surrounded by some of the main avenues of the metropolis, San Pedro de los Pinos offers easy access to all points of interest, whether you want to visit cultural sites, shopping centers like Plaza Metrópoli or Costco, parks, or renowned restaurants.

Moreover, San Pedro de los Pinos stands out for its safe and welcoming environment. Its tree-lined streets invite you to stroll and enjoy authentic local life. You will find a wide variety of gastronomic options, from traditional street vendors to modern high-end restaurants, and above all, the emblematic San Pedro de los Pinos market in front of Pombo Park

name: Cozy house in Coyoacan center, Casa Aguacate
description:
Welcome to Aguacate 96-B a charming house in the heart of the legendary Callejon del Aguacate, one of the most iconic alleys in Mexico City.
This cozy colonial style house has a one master bedroom with a terrace, bathroom, and a beautiful living and sitting room area with a lovely terrace to enjoy your morning coffee or just relax in the hammock.
The house is just round the corner from Francisco Sosa street, known for its beautiful colonial houses and cosy restaurants.
neighborhood_overview:
Located in the legendary Callejon del Aguacate, this charming house sits in the heart of Coyoacan, one of the most beautiful neighbourhoods in Mexico City.
The house is just a few minute walk from downtown Coyoacan, where you have a a number of delicious restaurants to choose from, local markets, and historic sites to visit.
It's also a walking distance from los Viveros, a huge park where local residents go for a jog, stroll, meditation, karate among other recreational activities.

To note is that Coyoacan is surrounded by a great variety of trees, plants, and flowers which some people might be allergic to. Although very beautiful, in the winter months all this vegetation can make the house pretty chilly.
